lamorous realities of industrial robotics—where uptime, maintenance, and cost dictate success, not viral videos.","keyPoints":["First commercial Atlas deployment at Hyundai Metaplant","Strength and precision still constrained by battery life","Demo choreography vs. real-world industrial chaos"],"source":{"name":"","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sd8ivhpjI6g"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/atlas-steps-out-of-the-labinto-hyundais-factory-fl/main.jpg","alt":"Atlas steps out of the lab—into Hyundai’s factory floor"},"subtitle":"Od laboratorijskih uvjeta do industrijske prakse: jaz koji ostaje između YouTube snimaka i stvarnog radnog dana","subtitleEn":"The gap between a polished video and a 24/7 assembly line","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/atlas-steps-out-of-the-labinto-hyundais-factory-fl/subtitle.png","alt":"The gap between a polished video and a 24/7 assembly line"},"tags":["Boston Dynamics","Humanoid Robotics","Industrial Automation"],"geo":{"name":"Ulsan, South Korea","lat":35.5384,"lon":129.3114,"countryCode":"KR"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$6","videoUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sd8ivhpjI6g"},{"id":"2026-03-23-demining-drones-show-promise-but-battery-life-is-a","dbId":612,"title":"Demining drones show promise, but battery life is a battlefield","titleEn":"Demining drones show promise, but battery life is a battlefield","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-23T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"The grim arithmetic is confirmed: at least 57 nations hold live antipersonnel mines, which killed 1,945 people and injured 4,325 in 2024 alone, 90% of them civilians.","execSummary":"The article dissects the gap between AI/drone demining demos and real-world deployment, focusing on hardware limits (battery, sensors, weather resilience), certification hurdles, and the persistent reliance on human verification. It challenges the narrative of 'revolutionary' tech by asking who actually benefits when prototypes fail in mud, rain, or dense vegetation—conditions where most mines actually exist.","keyPoints":["At least 57 nations still contain live land mines","105,640 mines cleared globally in 2024","AI-drone pairing faces critical hardware constraints"],"source":{"name":"TechXplore Robotics","url":"https://techxplore.com/news/2026-03-combining-drones-ai-faster-safer.html"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/demining-drones-show-promise-but-battery-life-is-a/main.jpg","alt":"Demining drones show promise, but battery life is a battlefield"},"subtitle":"Od demo videa do prave deminacije: koliko je to stvarno skalabilno?","subtitleEn":"From a lab to a field","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/demining-drones-show-promise-but-battery-life-is-a/subtitle.jpg","alt":"From a lab to a field"},"tags":["Mine Clearance","Drone Technology","Autonomous Demining","Explosive Ordnance Disposal"],"geo":{"name":"Bosna i Hercegovina","lat":43.9159,"lon":17.6791,"countryCode":"XX"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$7","part1En":"$8","part2En":"$9"},{"id":"2026-03-22-bristol-s-motor-networks-mimic-musclebut-can-they-","dbId":587,"title":"Bristol's Motor Networks Mimic Muscle—But Can They Deploy?","titleEn":"Bristol's Motor Networks Mimic Muscle—But Can They Deploy?","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Scientists at the University of Bristol have built a network of mechanical motors that replicates how human muscle fibers recruit under increasing load.","execSummary":"Bristol researchers built a mechanical motor network mimicking human muscle behavior under load—impressive in theory, but real-world deployment faces hardware limits, scalability costs, and environmental durability gaps. The article dissects the divide between lab demos and industrial readiness, targeting engineers who need to separate hype from viable tech.","keyPoints":["Mechanical motor networks replicate muscle fiber recruitment","Journal of Royal Society Interface publishes findings","Hardware durability remains unproven outside lab"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/bristol-s-motor-networks-mimic-musclebut-can-they-/main.jpg","alt":"Bristol's Motor Networks Mimic Muscle—But Can They Deploy?"},"subtitle":"Demo izgleda obećavajuće, ali može li preživjeti mokri utorak u industriji?","subtitleEn":"From controlled demo to deployment reality","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/bristol-s-motor-networks-mimic-musclebut-can-they-/subtitle.jpg","alt":"From controlled demo to deployment reality"},"tags":["Muscle Network","Humanoid Robotics","Industrial Automation"],"geo":{"name":"Bristol, United Kingdom","lat":51.454514,"lon":-2.58791,"countryCode":"GB"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$a","part1En":"$b","part2En":"$c"},{"id":"2026-03-22-solar-farm-robots-can-they-survive-outside-the-dem","dbId":571,"title":"Solar farm robots: Can they survive outside the demo?","titleEn":"Solar farm robots: Can they survive outside the demo?","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"The US solar industry needs to move faster—[1.","execSummary":"Terabase Energy's Terafab V2 solar construction robot has completed field testing and is now commercially available, marking a potential shift from demo-controlled robotics to real-world deployment. The system's ability to operate autonomously in uncontrolled environments will determine whether this represents genuine industrial automation progress.","keyPoints":["Autonomous solar farm builder exits field testing","AI-driven construction claims 2x speed over humans","Hardware limits: terrain, payload, and maintenance reality"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/solar-farm-robots-can-they-survive-outside-the-dem/main.jpg","alt":"Solar farm robots: Can they survive outside the demo?"},"subtitle":"Od kontroliranog testa do prašnjavog gradilišta","subtitleEn":"Od labsa do prakse: Terafab V2 obećava brže gradnje, ali stvari postaju zanimljive kad padne kiša.","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/solar-farm-robots-can-they-survive-outside-the-dem/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Od labsa do prakse: Terafab V2 obećava brže gradnje, ali stvari postaju zanimljive kad padne kiša."},"tags":["Terafab V2","Solar Farm Maintenance","Industrial Automation"],"geo":{"name":"San Francisco, US","lat":37.7749,"lon":-122.4194,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$d","part1En":"$e","part2En":"$f"},{"id":"2026-03-22-ukraines-drones-can-they-outfly-dji-without-chinas","dbId":568,"title":"Ukraine’s drones: Can they outfly DJI without China’s chips?","titleEn":"Ukraine’s drones: Can they outfly DJI without China’s chips?","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-22T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"The US Army’s [Drone Dominance program](https://www.","execSummary":"The US Army's billion-dollar bet on Ukrainian drones isn't just about avoiding Chinese components—it's a high-stakes test of whether non-Chinese hardware can meet real-world military demands. The Shrike 10 Fiber and F10 models impress on paper, but their deployment readiness hinges on unproven scalability, maintenance logistics, and durability in harsh environments, exposing the gap between procurement decisions and operational reality.","keyPoints":["Pentagon bets $1B on non-Chinese drones from Ukraine","Shrike 10 Fiber’s hardware limits remain untested at scale","DJI’s supply chain dominance isn’t just about components"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/ukraines-drones-can-they-outfly-dji-without-chinas/main.jpg","alt":"Ukraine’s drones: Can they outfly DJI without China’s chips?"},"subtitle":"Od labsa do prakse: Koliko su ukrajinski dronovi spremni za stvarne misije?","subtitleEn":"Od labsa do prakse: Ukrajinski dronovi moraju dokazati više od ‘bez-kineske’ etikete","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/ukraines-drones-can-they-outfly-dji-without-chinas/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Od labsa do prakse: Ukrajinski dronovi moraju dokazati više od ‘bez-kineske’ etikete"},"tags":["Ukrainian Drones","DJI","Military Drone Deployment"],"geo":{"name":"San Francisco, US","lat":37.7749,"lon":-122.4194,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$10","part1En":"$11","part2En":"$12"},{"id":"2026-03-20-accidental-hacker-gets-30k-for-7-000-robot-securit","dbId":562,"title":"Accidental Hacker Gets $30K for 7,000-Robot Security Flaw","titleEn":"Accidental Hacker Gets $30K for 7,000-Robot Security Flaw","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"A man attempting to control his DJI robot vacuum with a PlayStation gamepad accidentally discovered he could access approximately 7,000 other devices—complete with camera feeds into strangers' homes.","execSummary":"A seemingly harmless PlayStation hack exposed 7,000 DJI robovacs to potential privacy breaches, revealing critical IoT scaling flaws. The incident highlights how demo-ready products often lack deployment-grade security, especially in cloud architecture—raising questions about DJI’s prioritization of speed over safety in mass-market robotics.","keyPoints":["Man accessed 7,000 robots with gamepad","DJI pays $30,000 bug bounty","Security flaw exposed home camera feeds"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/accidental-hacker-gets-30k-for-7-000-robot-securit/main.jpg","alt":"Accidental Hacker Gets $30K for 7,000-Robot Security Flaw"},"subtitle":"Kada hobi postane sigurnosni incident: što nam ovo govori o IoT skaliranju","subtitleEn":"The $30,000 Question Behind 7,000 Exposed Robots","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/accidental-hacker-gets-30k-for-7-000-robot-securit/subtitle.jpg","alt":"The $30,000 Question Behind 7,000 Exposed Robots"},"tags":["DJI","Drone Hacking","IoT Security"],"geo":{"name":"Shenzhen, China","lat":22.5431,"lon":114.0579,"countryCode":"CN"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$13","part1En":"A man attempting to control his DJI robot vacuum with a PlayStation gamepad accidentally discovered he could access approximately 7,000 other devices—complete with camera feeds into strangers' homes. DJI has confirmed it will pay $30,000 for the discovery, turning an unsettling security nightmare into a lucrative bug bounty. The Valentine's Day incident, [first reported by The Verge](https://www.theverge.com), exposes the fragile security architecture underlying connected home robotics.\nThis wasn't sophisticated hacking. The researcher simply wanted to steer his own device using alternative input methods. What he found was an exposed network infrastructure that apparently required no authentication to access other users' robots. According to available information, the vulnerability would have allowed remote viewing through onboard cameras—a privacy breach of staggering scale. The gap between what these devices promise and how they're secured remains embarrassingly wide.","part2En":"$14"},{"id":"2026-03-20-electronic-dolphin-a-robot-that-fits-in-your-shoeb","dbId":554,"title":"Electronic Dolphin: A robot that fits in your shoe—but can it survive Tuesday?","titleEn":"Electronic Dolphin: A robot that fits in your shoe—but can it survive Tuesday?","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Engineers at RMIT University have unveiled the 'Electronic Dolphin,' a remote-controlled minibot roughly the size of a sneaker designed to tackle oil spills.","execSummary":"RMIT’s sneaker-sized ‘Electronic Dolphin’ robot uses a sea-urchin-inspired filter to clean oil spills, but its real-world applicability is constrained by battery life, scalability, and controlled-testing limitations. The article dissects the gap between demo capabilities and deployment readiness, focusing on niche use cases (ports, coastal areas) while questioning hardware durability and operational costs—critical for an industry where seconds and reliability matter more than innovation hype.","keyPoints":["Sneaker-sized robot targets oil spills","Sea urchin-inspired filters hoover crude","Demo vs deployment gap remains wide"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/electronic-dolphin-a-robot-that-fits-in-your-shoeb/main.jpg","alt":"Electronic Dolphin: A robot that fits in your shoe—but can it survive Tuesday?"},"subtitle":"Od labsa do prakse: koliko je ovaj ‘delfin’ spreman za prljave poslove?","subtitleEn":"Od labsa do prakse: što nedostaje za pravi deployment?","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/electronic-dolphin-a-robot-that-fits-in-your-shoeb/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Od labsa do prakse: što nedostaje za pravi deployment?"},"tags":["Oil Spill Cleanup","Marine Robotics","Autonomous Underwater Vehicle"],"geo":{"name":"Melbourne, Australia","lat":-37.8136,"lon":144.9631,"countryCode":"AU"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$15","part1En":"$16","part2En":"$17"},{"id":"2026-03-20-faa-greenlights-real-world-air-taxi-testing-across","dbId":548,"title":"FAA Greenlights Real-World Air Taxi Testing Across 26 States","titleEn":"FAA Greenlights Real-World Air Taxi Testing Across 26 States","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-20T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"After years of certification gridlock, the FAA has finally approved eight pilot programs across 26 states that will let Archer, Joby, and other eVTOL manufacturers begin real-world testing this summer.","execSummary":"The FAA’s approval of eight eVTOL pilot programs marks a shift from controlled demos to real-world testing—but the gap between a polished video and scalable deployment remains vast. This analysis cuts through the hype to examine hardware limits (battery life, payload, autonomy), regulatory hurdles, and the few use cases (like medical cargo) where the tech might actually deliver near-term value.","keyPoints":["Eight pilot programs across 26 states approved","Archer and Joby begin summer flight trials","Certification bottleneck finally shows movement"],"source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/faa-greenlights-real-world-air-taxi-testing-across/main.jpg","alt":"FAA Greenlights Real-World Air Taxi Testing Across 26 States"},"subtitle":"Od odobrenih programa do stvarnog letenja: koliko je to od demo-a do deploymenta?","subtitleEn":"From press release to payload: testing begins, but certification remains the real bottleneck","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/faa-greenlights-real-world-air-taxi-testing-across/subtitle.jpg","alt":"From press release to payload: testing begins, but certification remains the real bottleneck"},"tags":["Air Taxi","FAA","Urban Air Mobility","Deployment","Regulation"],"geo":{"name":"United States, US","lat":39.8283,"lon":-98.5795,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$18","part1En":"$19","part2En":"$1a"},{"id":"2026-03-16-4d-vision-on-a-chip-what-the-demo-doesn-t-show","dbId":399,"title":"4D Vision on a Chip: What the Demo Doesn't Show","titleEn":"4D Vision on a Chip: What the Demo Doesn't Show","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-16T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-16T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"Half a million microscopic components on a single silicon chip.","execSummary":"A new compact imaging sensor promises 4D vision for robots by combining 3D mapping with velocity measurement, but its real-world applicability remains uncertain. The article explores the gap between lab demonstrations and practical deployment, analyzing hardware limitations, scalability challenges, and potential industrial use cases.","source":{"name":"","url":""},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/4d-vision-on-a-chip-what-the-demo-doesn-t-show/main.jpg","alt":"4D Vision on a Chip: What the Demo Doesn't Show"},"subtitle":"Od labsa do prakse: što ovaj kompaktni senzor zaista može?","subtitleEn":"From Lab Bench to Assembly Line","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/4d-vision-on-a-chip-what-the-demo-doesn-t-show/subtitle.jpg","alt":"From Lab Bench to Assembly Line"},"tags":["4D Vision","Robotic Perception","Computer Vision","Silicon Chip","Autonomy"],"geo":{"name":"Global","lat":0,"lon":0,"countryCode":"XX"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$1b","part1En":"$1c","part2En":"$1d"},{"id":"2026-03-10-ais-new-control-knob-less-data-more-precisionif-yo","dbId":206,"title":"AI’s new ‘control knob’: Less data, more precision—if you know how to use it","titleEn":"AI’s new ‘control knob’: Less data, more precision—if you know how to use it","category":"robotics","date":"2026-03-10T12:00:00Z","scrapeDateDate":"2026-03-10T12:00:00Z","excerpt":"For years, building multimodal AI—systems that juggle text, images, audio, and more—has been a high-stakes guessing game.","execSummary":"Emory physicists' unified mathematical framework for multimodal AI offers a practical way to reduce data and compute costs—critical for robotics and smaller teams. The article examines whether this shift from trial-and-error to systematic optimization will translate into real-world efficiency gains or remain confined to academic research.","source":{"name":"Future Pulse","url":"https://futurepulse.hr"},"image":{"url":"/images/articles/ais-new-control-knob-less-data-more-precisionif-yo/main.jpg","alt":"AI’s new ‘control knob’: Less data, more precision—if you know how to use it"},"subtitle":"Novi matematički okvir može smanjiti troškove i povećati točnost – ali će ga industrija prihvatiti?","subtitleEn":"A physics-inspired framework cuts through multimodal AI’s trial-and-error mess. Who benefits first?","subtitleImage":{"url":"/images/articles/ais-new-control-knob-less-data-more-precisionif-yo/subtitle.jpg","alt":"A physics-inspired framework cuts through multimodal AI’s trial-and-error mess. Who benefits first?"},"tags":["future-pulse","automated","robotics"],"geo":{"name":"Atlanta, United States","lat":33.749,"lon":-84.388,"countryCode":"US"},"featured":false,"approved":true,"content":"$1e","part1En":"$1f","part2En":"$20"}]}]]}],["$L21"],"$L22"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
